## Findings

### [MINOR] No commit between RED (Task 3) and GREEN (Task 4)
**Description:** Task 3 writes and runs the failing integration tests (RED) but has
no commit step. The test file tests/integration/test_backtest_replay.py is not
committed until Task 5 Step 4, after both RecordingModule and ReplayBus are
implemented. Best practice per TDD discipline is to commit the RED test file before
writing any implementation so the failing state is preserved in git history. This is
not a hard project-guidelines rule but weakens the audit trail.
**Location:** Task 3 (missing commit step); Task 5, Step 4 (first commit of test file)
**Fix required:** Add a commit step at the end of Task 3:
  git add tests/integration/test_backtest_replay.py
  git commit -m "test(python): add backtest replay integration tests (RED)"
This is not blocking.

## Summary

The plan is structurally sound and faithful to the spec. All spec constraints are
correctly represented: `clock` is keyword-only with `LiveClock()` default and is not
added to ModuleConfig; heartbeat timing in `Module.run()` is unchanged; RecordingModule
uses `self._sub_sock.setsockopt(zmq.SUBSCRIBE, b"")` directly (not `self.subscribe("")`);
overrides `_dispatch(self, topic: str, payload: bytes)` per the eng-review-corrected
signature (not `raw_frames: list`); captures `wall_ns = time.time_ns()` at the top of
`_dispatch()` before the super call; record format is `[topic, timestamp_ns, payload,
wall_ns]` with `timestamp_ns = self._clock.now_ns()`; ReplayBus is a plain class (not a
Module subclass) with `self._ctx` created in `__init__` and terminated in `run()`; the
3-frame Bus envelope is correct; the delay formula and `speed=0.0` guard match the spec;
test ports 35556/35557/35558/35559 match the spec. TDD structure is correctly followed
across all tasks. File ownership is confined to `tyche/backtest/`, `tyche/core/module.py`,
and `tests/` — no Rust files are touched. The single minor finding does not block
implementation.

Result: APPROVED
